cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV

This paper is about improving the ability of neural networks to learn compositional language, which is a fundamental problem in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a novel approach that involves generating attention maps and mapping attended input words to output symbols, which suggests that it may be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on NLP tasks that involve understanding and generating natural language instructions, which could also be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) tasks that involve interpreting visual instructions.
